LSE-listed Gem Diamonds has recovered a high-quality 370 ct Type II white diamond from the Letšeng mine in Lesotho. This follows the company's announcement on May 4 of the recovery of a high-quality 254 ct Type II white diamond. Gem notes on its website that the Letšeng mine is renowned for its production of large, top colour, exceptional white diamonds, making it the highest average dollar per carat kimberlite diamond mine in the world. 